x, y \in \mathbb{R}^n
(A - \lambda) z = 0 \implies \left((A - \mu) - i\nu\right)(x + iy) = 0 \implies \begin{cases}(A-\mu) x + \nu y = 0\\(A - \mu) y - \nu x = 0\end{cases}
x^T(A-\mu)x + y^T(A-\mu)y = \nu (y^T x - x^T y) = 0
